  "instructions": [
    "Heat oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add rice wine vinegar, mushrooms, scallions, and garlic. Stir-fry until the vegetables are tender but still crisp.",
    "Remove from heat and stir in soy sauce, light rum (if using), and cornstarch mixture to thicken. Mix well and let simmer for a minute or two until thickened.",
    "Gently add cubed tofu and cook until heated through, about 3-5 minutes.",
    "Serve hot with nori seaweed slices if desired."
